	aFatherHeading={`A Father for the Jewish people`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here is something your own Scriptures say with stunning tenderness: the Holy One, blessed be He — the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob — is not only King and Judge and Lawgiver. He is also a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong>. "Is He not your Father, who created you?" asks Moses in Deuteronomy 32:6. "You, O LORD, are our Father," cries Isaiah (63:16; 64:8). This is not a borrowed idea — it was first revealed to your people, in your books, in your prayers.</p><p>To honor the Fatherhood of God is not to leave the awe behind. It is to discover that the same transcendent One who thunders on Sinai also bends down like a father teaching a child to walk (Hosea 11:3). The God who is utterly holy is also utterly tender. Both are true, and your prophets held them together without contradiction.</p><p>So before the world ever spoke of God as Father, your Scriptures did. The Father's Heart Bible™ simply lets that nearness be heard clearly — a fresh English translation that brings out the Father-heart of God wherever your own Scriptures reveal it. It comes humbly, with deep respect, as an invitation: the God you revere from afar longs to be known up close.</p>`}
