		{ heading: `A Father, not only a Sovereign`, bodyHtml: `"You, O LORD, are our Father." In <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/isaiah/64" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Isaiah 64</a>, the prophet reaches past the throne to the heart — the same holy God you revere calls Himself the potter who shapes you with a father's care.` },
		{ heading: `Compassion measured like a father's`, bodyHtml: `<a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/103" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Psalm 103</a> says God's mercy toward His people is like a father's compassion for his children — nearness offered without ever diminishing His holiness.` },
		{ heading: `A love that began in tenderness`, bodyHtml: `"When Israel was a child, I loved him." <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/hosea/11" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Hosea 11</a> remembers God teaching His people to walk, lifting them like a parent lifts a little one to His cheek — the covenant rooted in affection.` },
